
=Typology=

Jeremy Santora:

"World-systems are totalities defined by the existence of a “single division of labor and multiple cultural systems”  (Wallerstein 1974b:390). They take two forms dependent on their political structure: 

* world-economies or 

* world-empires. 

World-economies are characterized by a heterogeneous political structure, linked economically. They 
tend to be unstable leading either to their disintegration or transformation into a world-empire through conquest. 
World-empires, by contrast, are characterized by a single political structure which administers its internal 
economic operations in a redistributive and tributary manner." 

(https://www.academia.edu/125747036/Lex_Capitalocenae_Cheap_Nature_and_the_Emergence_of_Legal_Naturalism_pre_publication_final_)


